{
  "text": "and substitution of the arginine with valine in AQP1 enabled H + permeability [CITATION_1] . In the less well understood, intracellular \"superaquaporins\" AQPs 11 and 12, arginine is replaced by leucine [CITATION_2] . Although functional studies of H + permeability in superaquaporins are yet to be reported, the loss of this arginine residue may suggest roles in intracellular H + homeostasis for AQPs 11 and 12.",
